04/04/2003
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- Border police units of Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro started joint control operations at the sea border in Prevlaka peninsula on Thursday (3 April). 
Police departments from Croatia's Dubrovnik-Nevetra and Montenegro's Herceg Novi districts sent two representatives each to the patrolling vessel. 
Under the plan, captains of the vessel would be rotated every two months. 
The countries signed the sea control agreement and related protocols in December. 
(Croatia - 03/04/03; 02/04/03)
